What youâ€™re looking for is **Hyprlandâ€™s â€œinitial workspace trackingâ€** feature.
It does *exactly* this: it remembers the workspace where an app was **launched**, even if the window appears later after youâ€™ve already switched away.

So you donâ€™t need a visual placeholder window â€” Hyprland will still tile the window on the workspace you started it from.

